First Lady Melania Trump and Second Lady Karen Pence will be visiting Fort Bragg in North Carolina to meet with Soldiers, Sailors, Airmen, and Marines. They will receive demonstrations of special operations capabilities, tour the base facilities, and receive a briefing on the selection and training of elite special operators. As part of the month of the military child, they will also visit with students at the middle school on the base. Before leaving, Melania Trump will deliver remarks thanking military personnel and families for their service and sacrifices. Both Melania Trump and Karen Pence expressed their admiration for the military and their families, and their eagerness to offer support and encouragement.